{"lemma":"مِدادٌ","slug":"مِدادٌ","root":"م.د.د","root_slug":"م-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/م-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مِداد","root":"مدد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38317"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ink","examples":[{"text":"قُل لَّوْ كَانَ الْبَحْرُ مِدَادًا لِّكَلِمَاتِ رَبِّي لَنَفِدَ الْبَحْرُ قَبْلَ أَن تَنفَدَ كَلِمَاتُ رَبِّي وَلَوْ جِئْنَا بِمِثْلِهِ مَدَدًا","english":"Say, \"If the sea were ink for [writing] the words of my Lord, the sea would be exhausted before the words of my Lord were exhausted, even if We brought the like of it as a supplement.\""}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dung, manure"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lamp oil"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"field bindweed (Convolvulus arvensis"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root م د د (m d d), whence مَدَّ (madda, “to extend, stretch, spread out”)."},"ipa":["/mi.daːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38317","headword_ar":"مِدَادٌ","root":"md","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything that is added in a thing, because of its utility:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this is the original signification accord. to old lexicologists. (MF.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ink;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niqosN","text_ar":"نِقْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiborN","text_ar":"حِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MF;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that with which one writes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb:) so called because it aids the writer: (IAmb, L:) this is the common acceptation of the word. (MF.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midaAdN","text_ar":"مِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midaAdu Als~iraAji","text_ar":"مِدَادُ السِّرَاجِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", A)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Oil"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is put into a lamp."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midaAdN","text_ar":"مِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midaAdN AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"مِدَادٌ الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", A)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dung:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manure composed of dung and ashes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust and dung,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of strong earth; and"},{"kind":"text","text":"simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust; and sand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midaAdN","text_ar":"مِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A row"},{"kind":"text","text":"of trees; not of palm-trees. (IAar, in TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usokuwbN","text_ar":"اُسْكُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode, manner, fashion, and form."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banawoA buyuwtahumo EalaY midaAdK waAHidK","text_ar":"بَنَوْا بُيُوتَهُمْ عَلَى مِدَادٍ وَاحِدٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They built their houses after one mode, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midaAdu qayosK","text_ar":"مِدَادُ قَيْسٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain game"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Arabs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of children."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanobaEivu fiY","text_ar":"يَنْبَعِثُ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHawoDi miyzaAbaAni midaAduhumaA A^anohaAru Aljan~api","text_ar":"الحَوْضِ مِيزَابَانِ مِدَادُهُمَا اَنْهَارُ الجَنَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two pipes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spouts, whereof the sources"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lit. the source"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the supply are the rivers of paradise, pour into the pond"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is without its precincts]; i. e., the rivers of paradise flow into those pipes, or spouts, and increase their flow, or make it copious, or abundant. (L, K. *) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midaAdN","text_ar":"مِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amid~apN","text_ar":"اَمِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) which signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large needles"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAl~u","text_ar":"مَسَالُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", M, L, TT; in the CK and a MS copy of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misaAk","text_ar":"مِسَاك"},{"kind":"text","text":"; in the TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAk","text_ar":"مَسَاك"},{"kind":"text","text":") ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are inserted"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the two sides of a piece of cloth when its manufacture is commenced."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, TT, K.) ―         -b10-  Also, the pl., The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"threads which compose the warp of a web."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","Msb","IAmb","A","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}